Jerklib is an event-driven IRC library that can be used to write an IRC bot/client.
Author: Jason Davis - mohadib@openactive.org
Big thanks to Robert O'Connor <robby.oconnor@gmail.com> for all the hard work!

SF Project Page: https://sourceforge.net/projects/jerklib/
HomePage: http://jerklib.sourceforge.net
Java Docs: http://jerklib.sourceforge.net/doc/

To run an example use one of the following commands:

This is the simplest example:
java -cp jerklib.jar jerklib.examples.Example

An example of a bot:
java -cp jerklib.jar jerklib.examples.jerkbot.jerkbot

There is also a Groovy example (a class written in groovy). To use it download
groovy from http://dist.groovy.codehaus.org/distributions/groovy-binary-1.5.4.zip
and unzip it to whereveer, then set up a GROOVY_HOME env. variable pointing to whereever
you unzipped toand put GROOVY_HOME/bin in your PATH.

To use the script you need to have the source handy and type:
                          
1) ant jar
2) groovy -cp bin/jerklib.jar jerklib/examples/groovy/jerkbot/Jerkbot.groovy

